l present.With noted contributions from Libby Adler, Chris Ashford, Matthew Ball, Noa Ben-Asher, Mary Anne Case, Brenda Cossman, Joseph J. Fischel, Janet Halley, Zachary Herz, Ratna Kapur, Ido Katri, Evelyn Kessler, Ummni Khan, Kyle Kirkup, Jennifer C. Nash, Senthorun Raj, and Matthew Waites.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aSexual minoritiesxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aLGBT rights.  aLavender Scare.  acriminalization.  acritical approaches to law.  acritical legal studies.  acritical race theory.  adecriminalization.  afeminist legal theory.  agender.  ahistory of sexuality.  alaw and sexuality.  anormativity and antinormativity.  aqueer legal studies.  aqueer theory.  aregulation.1 aCossman, Brenda, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFischel, Joseph J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479807635.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479807635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479807635/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles